@node cars "Cars on these disks"

                          @{u} Cars On These Disks

Disk 1:

Supra@{uu}

This is a mean, sleek supercar, based on the new Toyota Supra, but it has
turned out looking a bit more like an F40 or Bugatti supercar now rendered.
It features large front air dam, massive wheels shod with ultra low profile
tyres and an outrageously big curved rear spoiler. Looks best in black.


@{u}Truck Cab@{uu}

This solid vehicle is a big truck, minus its trailer. Includes tall
vertical exhaust pipes, 8 litre diesel engine and lots of wheels (6).
Always wins in colisions with cars.


@{u}DISK 2:@{uu}

@{u}Land Rover@{uu}

The classic Land Rover is still going strong today after 20 odd years and
is the ultimate rugged 4x4 off road machine. Includes original two tone
paint work.


@{u}Wheel Chair@{uu}

Not for the faint hearted. Choose this vehicle and you are placed in
control of a crappy 20 year old NHS wheelchair. Very funny when driven
head on into Trucks, Buses, Tanks etc.

@{"Cars Available For Just Ł8" link extracars}

@endnode

@node extracars "Cars Sent With Upgrade"

                           @{u}Extra Car Disks@{uu}


If you @{"upgrade" link upgrading} your Skidmarks Car disks, for the bargain
price of just Ł6, you will get these extra TWELVE vehicles.

See the "Upgrade Vehicles" drawer on Car Disk 2 for previews of the 12
extra cars available.


@{u}Cosworth@{uu}

This rally machine is somewhere between an Escort Cosworth and an Aston
Martin Vantage, two of my favourite cars. It features an enormous whale
tail rear spoiler. This car was a winner in the Amiga Format Imagine Built
My Hotrod Competition. Unfortunately it wasn't included in Skidmarks 2, but
it is now.


@{u}Dragster@{uu}

A top fuel 2000 HP dragster. Not too good on bends. Engine tends to blow up
after a few laps. Features include parachute assisted braking system.


@{u}Tank@{uu}

Literally crush the opposition in this 8 ton, 6 litre, V8 piece of military
hardware. Features include go anywhere capability, and bullet proof
undentable body panels. Cannon shells are an optional extra.


@{u}Dick Dastardly Car@{uu}

I can't remember exactly what his car was like but this is probably the
kind of thing he would drive. Features rocket engine and jet fighter
design, suspended 6 feet above the road on long legs for unfair overtaking
advantage. Muttly not included.


@{u}Reliant Robin@{uu}

Race this classic three wheeler at break-neck speeds. Features include one
wheel drive for extra off road ability, single cylinder 500cc engine for
ease of maintenance, and a highly advanced, light weight, silicon fibre
composite bodyshell (fibreglass) to fight corrosion as you are left on the
starting line.


@{u}Bus@{uu}

Now 800 people can participate in a game of Skidmarks! Each double decker
bus comes with 100 passengers free of charge. These are no crumbly old
Routemasters either, but brand new hi-tec, top of the range racing
machines.


@{u}JCB@{uu}

Ever wanted to get rid of an annoying bump or re-sculpt your favourite
Skidmarks track? With this authentic JCB earth mover you can now carry out
essential maintenance repairs to your tracks. Features front and rear
buckets, only available in yellow. Max speed, 19 mph.


@{u}Roller Scater@{uu}

Take control of this roller skater with a death wish. High speed head on
colisions with buses are funny, as you watch your maniac on wheels become
a blob of human mess on the windscreen


@{u}Go-Kart@{uu}

Small one cylinder go-kart, very fast, light and manoeuvrable. No room for
passengers though. This is not the Imagine object already supplied with
Skidmarks 2


@{u}Convertible@{uu}

A classic American 2 seater convertible cruiser, with full interior detail
and complete with driver on the wrong side. Not very good in wet wether.


@{u}Fighter Jet@{uu}

Fly your F-466452/a at Mach 20, 3 feet above ground level. Features twin
20000 hp engines, an arsenal of heat seeking missiles, and machine gun with
5000 rounds of ammunition.

@{u}Big Foot@{uu}

The monster trucks already supplied with Skidmarks don't really have very
big wheels. This one does. The ultimate traffic jam beater/ pedestrian
squasher.

@endnode





